    <section xml:id="print-article">
        <title>Print Article</title>
        <introduction>
            <sidebyside width="50%">
                <image source="images/Citations-PrintArticle"/>
            </sidebyside>
        </introduction>
        <subsection>
            <title>APA</title>
            <p indent="hanging"><red>Author last name, initials.</red> <lightgreen>(Year of publication).</lightgreen> <lightblue>Title of Article.</lightblue> <pink><booktitle>Name of Journal</booktitle></pink> <darkred>volume(issue),</darkred> <blue>page range.</blue></p>
            <p indent="hanging"><red>Mann, S. A.</red> <lightgreen>(2011).</lightgreen> <lightblue>Pioneers of U.S. ecofeminism and environmental justice.</lightblue> <pink><booktitle>Feminist Formations</booktitle></pink> <darkred>23(2),</darkred> <blue>1<ndash/>25.</blue></p>
            <p>In-text: (Mann, 2011)</p>
            <p>For an article found in an online journal, include the DOI<mdash/>or, if the article has no DOI, write Retrieved from the URL<mdash/>after the page range. Do not place a period at the end of the DOI or URL.</p>
        </subsection>
        <subsection>
